All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AuthController
The AuthController class handles user authentication processes for the CAMs system.
AuthService
The AuthService implements IAuthService, and is an abstract class that also provides functionality to verify password.
AuthStaffService
The AuthStaffService extends AuthService, and provides log in functionality for staff.
AuthStore
The AuthStore class is responsible for managing authentication-related information, specifically the currently logged-in user in the application.
AuthStudentService
The AuthStudentService extends AuthService, and provides log in functionality for staff.
Camp
The Camp class defines a camp with various attributes such as ID, name, dates, visibility, closing date, user group, location, slots, staff information, committee, registered students, and a description.
CampStaffService
The CampStaffService implements ICampStaffService, and provides camp related functionalities for staff.
CampStudentService
The CampStudentService implements ICampStudentService, and provides camp related functionalities for staff.
CampView
The CampView class provides methods for printing camps and its attributes to CLI.
CCMController
The CCMController class handles user interactions for the Camp Committee Members (which are Students with enum set to CCM).
DataStore
The DataStore class serves as a central storage for various model instances in the application.
EnquiryRequest
The EnquiryRequest class defines an enquiry request that students will create on a specific camp.
EnquiryRequestService
The EnquiryRequestService implements IRequestService, and provides request related functionalities for enquires.
FileService
The FileServices class provides methods for reading user data from CSV files and generating CSV files from Camp objects.
IAuthService
The IAuthService interface defines a contract for managing authentication services, such as login and logout.
ICampStaffService
The ICampStaffService interface defines a contract for staff related camp services.
ICampStudentService
The ICampStudentService interface defines a contract for student related camp services.
InputParser
The InputParser class provides utility methods for parsing user input.
IRequestService
The IRequestService interface defines a contract for managing requests.
MainApp
Entry point of the program.
MenuView
The MenuView class provides methods for displaying menu-related views in the CAMs system.
RangeChecker<T>
The RangeChecker class is a generic class used to determine if a value of type T is bounded by any range in a list.
Request
The Request class defines a request object which contains the IDs of the requester and responder, the contents of the request and a RequestStatus enum to indicate the status of the request.
RequestStatus
The RequestStatus enumeration represents the various states a request can be in.
RequestView
The RequestView provides functions to print out the content of a request to CLI.
Staff
The Staff class represents a staff member with additional attributes such as owned camps.
StaffController
The StaffController class handles user interactions for the Staff.
Student
The Student class represents a student with additional attributes such as camps, previous camps, committee membership, and points (applicable if the role is CCM).
StudentController
The StudentController class handles user interactions for the Students.
SuggestionRequest
The SuggestionRequest class defines an suggestion request that CCMs will create on a specific camp.
SuggestionRequestService
The SuggestionRequestService implements IRequestService, and provides request related functionalities for suggestions.
User
The User class represents a user with attributes such as userID, password, faculty, default password status, and role.
UserController
The UserController class provides a way to change password.
UserGroup
The UserGroup enumeration represents different user groups or faculties.
UserRole
The UserRole enumeration represents different roles that a user can have.
